# Overview

This playbook documents the exact process used to build, brand, and deploy the Escalation Advisor — a Claude-powered web tool. Use it as a repeatable template for every future app build.

The process covers four phases: project setup, building the tool, branding it, and deploying it publicly. Each section includes the exact steps, the decisions made, and the lessons learned the hard way.

## Final Architecture

| Component | What it is | URL / Location | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Team app | Main branch, no key input | escalation-advisor.vercel.app | API key in Vercel env vars |
| Public demo | Byok branch, gate screen | escalation-advisor-public.vercel.app | Users bring their own key |
| Public repo | GitHub, open source | github.com/kaitwaite/escalation-advisor | Fork main to deploy your own |

