## 6. Commit Message Convention

Format: [type]: [what you did in plain English]. Lowercase. Present tense. No period.

| TYPE | WHEN TO USE | EXAMPLE |
| --- | --- | --- |
| add: | New file, feature, or section | add: escalation brief output with mustard border |
| update: | Changed existing content | update: governance section in playbook |
| fix: | Corrected something broken | fix: byok branch missing Change Key button |
| remove: | Deleted something | remove: stale weekly meal plan files |
| docs: | README or documentation only | docs: add lessons learned to openclaw-starter |
| style: | Visual/formatting, no logic change | style: tighten card padding on mobile |
| refactor: | Restructured without behavior change | refactor: extract gate screen to component |
| deploy: | Deployment-related changes | deploy: trigger vercel redeploy after env var update |

