## How to connect a custom domain in Vercel

Repeat these steps for every new app and every new branch deployment.

Step 1 — Add the domain in Vercel

vercel.com -> project -> Settings -> Domains

Type: [repo-name].katehaan.dev -> Add

Copy the CNAME value Vercel gives you

Step 2 — Add the DNS record in Squarespace

squarespace.com -> Domains -> katehaan.dev -> DNS Settings -> Add Record

Type:  CNAME

Name:  [repo-name]          (e.g. escalation-advisor)

Value: [paste from Vercel]

Save

Step 3 — Verify and test

Wait 5-10 minutes -> Refresh in Vercel -> green = done

Test the URL in your browser

Step 4 — Update all references

README: replace .vercel.app URL with .katehaan.dev URL

Commit: update: migrate to katehaan.dev custom domain

Also update: LinkedIn, GitHub profile README, katehaan.dev portfolio site

| LESSON LEARNED  tone-fixer.vercel.app was claimed by someone else before custom domains were set up. This is why .vercel.app URLs are never shared publicly. Always set up the custom domain before sharing any link. |
