# Troubleshooting Guide

| Error | Fix |
| --- | --- |
| Something went wrong. Please try again. | Check Vercel logs. Almost always a missing or wrong ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var. Delete and re-add it, then redeploy. |
| Could not resolve authentication method | env var name is wrong or not set. Must be exactly ANTHROPIC_API_KEY. Redeploy after fixing. |
| Vulnerable version of Next.js detected | Update Next.js to the latest patched version. Check vercel.com/kb/bulletin/react2shell for the correct version. Also update React to ^19. |
| Unexpected token `main` | Syntax error in page.tsx — the JSX is broken. Rewrite the file from scratch. Never use sed or regex to modify TSX files. |
| No Output Directory named "public" | Vercel is treating it as a static site. Go to Settings → General → Framework Preset → set to Next.js → save → redeploy. |
| remote origin already exists | Run: git remote remove origin — then add the correct remote and push again. |
| Repository not found | The remote URL is wrong or the repo doesn't exist on GitHub yet. Create it first at github.com/new, then push. |
| fatal: not a git repository | Run git init first before any other git commands. |
| no upstream branch | Run: git push --set-upstream origin main |

